properties.alive_and_rescued_notes: Video and photos sent to AZWH who requested turtle be taken in - TITR trying to organise transport.

properties.injury_desc:
Head and tail missing
Shark feeding marks all over 
Presumed that both the head and tail was predated on prior to stranding on beach

properties.abnormalities_desc: Some peeling scutes, low energy, difficulty holding head up, weak.

properties.injury_desc:
Possible boat strike injury
Carapace falling apart into pieces
Scute peeling away - suggesting that the injury is possibly not fresh
properties.cause_of_stranding: Fractures/impact damage, (e.g. collisions, trawling or related boating activities)

properties.fouling_epibionts_desc: Barncales on carapace and soft tissue as well
properties.injury_desc: left front flipper with significant lacerations, showed some healing, potentially predator injury

properties.fouling_epibionts_desc: algae and barnacles including barnacles on soft tissue

properties.injury_desc: Fishing line wrapped around body forward of the blowhole and trailing line and 2 lures towards the peduncle. Line is not restricting movement. See photo's attached.
properties.cause_of_stranding: Hooked/entangled in fishing line or ingested fishing line

properties.fouling_epibionts_desc: Heavy barnacle load on carapace with mud and some barnacles on plastron
properties.alive_and_rescued_notes: kayakers brought turtle in off the sandbar to the boat ramp. Was lethargic when first approached. MOP said they placed animal in the water but it turned around and came back out of the water.
